body:
I seem to have bumped into a similar issue to #96 when trying to compile a simple project that contains a memory model from Microchip for the 23K640 SPI SRSAM.

My simple design looks like this:

// We need this since the specific memory module sets timescale.
`timescale 1ns/10ps

module simple();

  //----------------------------------------------------------------
  // Parameters.
  //----------------------------------------------------------------
  reg  mem_si;
  wire mem_so;
  reg  mem_sck;
  reg  mem_hold_n;
  reg  mem_reset;


  //----------------------------------------------------------------
  // Memory model.
  //----------------------------------------------------------------
  M23K640 memory(.SI(mem_si),
                 .SO(mem_so),
                 .SCK(mem_sck),
                 .CS_N(mem_cs_n),
                 .HOLD_N(mem_hold_n),
                 .RESET(mem_reset)
                );


  //----------------------------------------------------------------
  // main
  //----------------------------------------------------------------
  initial
    begin : main
      $display("Simple mem test bench started.");
      $display("");

      mem_si     = 1'h1;
      mem_sck    = 1'h0;
      mem_hold_n = 1'h1;
      mem_reset  = 1'h1;

      $display("");
      $display("Simple mem test bench completed.");
      $finish;
    end // main

endmodule // simple

The specific memory model can be downloaded here:
https://www.microchip.com/wwwproducts/en/23A640

Direct link to the zip file with the 23K640.v model:
http://ww1.microchip.com/downloads/en/DeviceDoc/23x640_Verilog_Model.zip

In the model, there is a set of dynamic delay statements (row 294 - 298):

   always @(DataShifterO) SO_DO <= #(tV) DataShifterO[07];

   bufif1 #(tV,0)    (OutputEnable1, SO_Enable, 1);
   notif1 #(tDIS)    (OutputEnable2, CS_N,   1);
   bufif1 #(tHV,tHZ) (OutputEnable3, HOLD_N, 1);


If I remove them, the compilation goes through.
